---
dops: v2
kind: skill

meta:
  name: argocd
  version: 2.2.0
  description: "Generate ArgoCD Application and ApplicationSet manifests"
  author: dojops
  license: MIT
  tags: [argocd, gitops, kubernetes, cd, deployment]

context:
  technology: ArgoCD
  fileFormat: yaml
  outputGuidance: |
    Generate valid ArgoCD Application or ApplicationSet YAML manifests.
    Output raw YAML content directly — do NOT wrap in JSON or code fences.
    Use multi-document YAML (--- separator) when generating multiple resources.
    The output must be valid kubectl-compatible YAML for ArgoCD CRDs.

    Generate appropriate ArgoCD resources based on the request:
    - **Application**: Single app deployment from a Git repo or Helm chart
    - **ApplicationSet**: Multi-cluster/multi-environment app generation
    - **AppProject**: RBAC boundaries and source/destination restrictions

    Structure each Application with:
    - apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1, kind: Application
    - metadata: name, namespace (argocd), labels, annotations, finalizers
    - spec.project: Target AppProject (default or custom)
    - spec.source: Git repo URL, path, targetRevision (or Helm chart)
    - spec.destination: Cluster URL/name, namespace
    - spec.syncPolicy: Automated sync, self-heal, prune, retry

    For ApplicationSet, include appropriate generators:
    - Git generator (directories or files)
    - Cluster generator (multi-cluster)
    - Matrix/Merge generators (combinations)
    - List generator (explicit environments)
  bestPractices:
    - Use the app-of-apps pattern for managing multiple applications
    - Enable automated sync with self-heal and prune for GitOps workflows
    - Configure sync waves (argocd.argoproj.io/sync-wave annotation) for ordering
    - Set ignoreDifferences for fields managed by controllers (e.g., replicas with HPA)
    - Use server-side apply for large manifests (ServerSideApply=true)
    - Configure retry strategy with backoff for transient failures
    - Add resource health checks with custom health.lua scripts when needed
    - Use AppProject to restrict source repos and destination clusters/namespaces
    - Set finalizers for cascade deletion (resources.finalizer.argocd.argoproj.io)
    - Use targetRevision with specific branches or tags, not HEAD in production
    - Configure notification triggers for sync status changes
    - Separate ArgoCD app definitions from application manifests in the repo
  context7Libraries:
    - name: argocd
      query: "ArgoCD Application ApplicationSet manifest, sync policy automated self-heal prune, sync waves, ignoreDifferences, AppProject, generators cluster git matrix"

files:
  - path: "{outputPath}/application.yaml"
    format: raw

detection:
  paths: ["**/argocd/*.yaml", "**/argocd/*.yml", "application.yaml", "applicationset.yaml"]
  updateMode: true

verification:
  structural:
    - path: "kind"
      required: true
      message: "ArgoCD manifest must have a kind (Application, ApplicationSet, or AppProject)"
    - path: "apiVersion"
      required: true
      message: "ArgoCD manifest must have apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1"

permissions:
  filesystem: write
  child_process: none
  network: none

scope:
  write: ["application.yaml", "applicationset.yaml", "appproject.yaml", "**/argocd/**/*.yaml", "**/argocd/**/*.yml"]

risk:
  level: MEDIUM
  rationale: "ArgoCD application changes affect Kubernetes deployment pipelines"

execution:
  mode: generate
  deterministic: false
  idempotent: true

update:
  strategy: replace
  inputSource: file
  injectAs: existingContent
---
# ArgoCD

## Prompt

You are an ArgoCD and GitOps expert. Generate production-ready ArgoCD Application and ApplicationSet manifests.

{outputGuidance}

Follow these best practices:
{bestPractices}

{context7Docs}

Project context: {projectContext}

## Keywords

argocd, gitops, application, applicationset, sync, deploy,
kubernetes, k8s, helm, kustomize, cd, continuous-delivery,
app-of-apps, sync-wave, self-heal, prune, project
